CONTEXT SearchGuard IN ENGLISH
PURPOSE CONTEXT SearchGuard
{+Test model for the authorisation of the full-text search module. It holds data
that an anonymous session has no interface to read: `Dossier` is only exposed
through an interface FOR Caseworker. `dossierNote` is non-univalent on purpose,
so the compiler stores it in its own binary table.+}

REPRESENT Note TYPE ALPHANUMERIC
REPRESENT Userid TYPE ALPHANUMERIC
REPRESENT Password TYPE PASSWORD
REPRESENT DateTime TYPE DATETIME

--[Data that requires the Caseworker role to read]--
RELATION dossierNote[Dossier*Note] -- non-UNI: stored in its own binary table

POPULATION dossierNote CONTAINS
   [ ("d1", "Vertrouwelijk medisch dossier van betrokkene")
   , ("d2", "Loonbeslag geheimhouding")
   ]

--[Minimal account model, so login can be enabled]--
RELATION accUserid[Account*Userid] [UNI]
RELATION accPassword[Account*Password] [UNI]
RELATION accIsActive[Account*Account] [PROP]
RELATION accMostRecentLogin[Account*DateTime] [UNI]
RELATION accLoginTimestamps[Account*DateTime]
RELATION sessionAccount[SESSION*Account] [UNI]

POPULATION accUserid CONTAINS [ ("alice", "alice") ]
POPULATION accPassword CONTAINS [ ("alice", "secret123") ]
POPULATION accIsActive CONTAINS [ ("alice", "alice") ]

--[Only a Caseworker can read dossiers]--
INTERFACE Dossiers FOR Caseworker : I[Dossier] cRud BOX<TABLE>
   [ "note" : dossierNote cRud
   ]

--[An anonymous landing page, so an anonymous session has an interface of its own]--
INTERFACE Welcome FOR Anonymous : "_SESSION"[SESSION] cRud BOX<TABLE>
   [ "hello" : I cRud
   ]

ENDCONTEXT
